postcontent: Argentine Hi Power In 1968/69, the Argentine military purchased a license to manufacture and sell a 9mm Hi Power made with Browning tooling,dies, and fixtures. The production training, engineering, and quality control would be supplied by Fabrique National ( FN) which manufactures Browning Hi Powers in Belgium. The Hi power design is a military/police pistol that was designed by John Browing in the early 1900s. My Hi Power was made in about 2003 based on serial number in and in an Argentine military factory(FM).  It evolved as the M95 which is the Browning Hi Power Mark IIIs. The magazine safety has been removed to improve the trigger pull to about 4.5 lbs.  The mag safety is sold with pistol.The pistol is single action and is in very nice condition. THe pistol comes with original box and manual. I have pictures which I can email. Any research I have done comes with the pistol. This is not a Hi Power copy as it was made on Browning tooling and parts can be had from FN in Belgium.The finish is baked on enamel with a phosphate coating.
